<h2 id="design-works" style="margin-bottom:0.5em">design works</h2>

<h3 id="poster-drafts">poster drafts</h3>

<p>2018 (month unknown), Adobe Illustrator CC. Back then, I was obsessed with late '90s/early '00s design Ã  la <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/dingridsystem/albums/72157630939112282">The Designers Republic</a> â€” chiefly, the microscopic typographic/diagrammatic details tucked away in the corners of their works. I liked to call these details <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greeble">"greeble"</a> â€” a prop design term for meaningless small details added to enhance the illusion of scale.</p>

<p>I started these posters by greebling around the corners to "frame" something in the middle â€” but I never got to making the middle parts.</p>

